description:
&lt;p&gt;A challenging and exciting opportunity waits for a dynamic, motivated and hardworking individual to work within Peritoneal Dialysis (PD) Unit at the Royal London Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As one of Britain’s biggest renal units and driven by our quest towards bringing excellence to life and providing high quality of service to PD patients, we are continuously working towards professional advancement which leads to expansion of the establishment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will have:&lt;br /&gt;- Relevant post registration experience&lt;br /&gt;- Relevant post specialist qualification or equivalent, (Renal Course ENB 136 is desirable).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This successful candidate will benefit from a specialist training in PD and will work closely with the interdisciplinary team. You will have the opportunity to work in various areas rotating from the clinical area, inpatient/acute areas, training &amp; community. This post will also partake in Practise Development and in raising PD’s profile within and outside the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lilian Ekeh - Senior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lilian.ekeh1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
